- encode: categorical columns with >2 unique categories (use one-hot). For columns with exactly two categories, map them to a single numeric column (e.g., 0/1) instead of producing multiple one-hot fields. Exclude anything already listed in drop_columns.

- impute: only columns that need missing-value handling. Allowed strategies: mean, median, most_frequent, constant.

- If unsure, leave a list empty.
